Lumbricillus lineatus
partim; 
Michaelsen 1900
: p. 80; 
Welch 1917
: pp. 123-130; 
Nielsen and Christensen 1959
: pp. 100-102, figs 109-112.

Genetically identified from the Netherlands, Norway, Spain and Sweden; also recognized from Canada (BIN-numbers BOLD:AAF9630 & BOLD:ACV7068). This species has historically been widely reported from Europe and North America, and even from the southern hemisphere (
Stephenson 1932b
).
